to be honest, since the introduction of themes years ago I've never tried to use a template without a theme.
What you can do if you don't want to utilize any of the theme capabilities is create a theme from scratch and put your template in there. The only files you need for creating a theme are:
• theme.json
• fields.json
Those files have to be on the root level of your theme. If you don't want to use theme fields, leave the fields.json empty.
The theme.json can be kept as simple as possible:
```{
	"label": "Theme",
	"preview_path": null,
	"screenshot_path": null,
	"enable_domain_stylesheets": false,
	"is_available_for_new_content": true,
	"responsive_breakpoints": [
		{
			"name": "mobile",
			"mediaQuery": "@media (max-width: 480px)",
			"previewWidth": {
				"value": 480
			}
		}
	],
	"author": {
		"name": "Anton Bujanowski",
		"email": "<mailto:some@email.com|some@email.com>",
		"company": ""
	}
}```
&lt;ou don't even need the responsive_breakpoints part... but it's recommended :slightly_smiling_face:
